## Pre-Existing Foundations

### Task 1: FallbackChunker

The simplest strategy — recursive separator cascade for unrecognized formats. Built first because the pipeline tests will use it as a real strategy.

**Files:**
- Create: `crates/corvia-kernel/src/chunking_fallback.rs`
- Modify: `crates/corvia-kernel/src/lib.rs` (add module declaration)

**Step 1: Write the failing test**

Create `crates/corvia-kernel/src/chunking_fallback.rs` with tests only:

```rust
//! FallbackChunker — recursive text splitting for unrecognized formats (D68).
//!
//! Splits text using a separator cascade: `\n\n` → `\n` → ` ` → character-level.
//! Produces chunks up to `max_tokens` using the chars/4 heuristic.

use corvia_common::errors::Result;
use crate::chunking_strategy::{ChunkingStrategy, ChunkMetadata, RawChunk, SourceMetadata};

pub struct FallbackChunker {
    max_tokens: usize,
}

impl FallbackChunker {
    pub fn new(max_tokens: usize) -> Self {
        Self { max_tokens }
    }
}

impl ChunkingStrategy for FallbackChunker {
    fn name(&self) -> &str { "fallback" }
    fn supported_extensions(&self) -> &[&str] { &[] }
    fn chunk(&self, _source: &str, _meta: &SourceMetadata) -> Result<Vec<RawChunk>> {
        todo!()
    }
}

#[cfg(test)]
mod tests {
    use super::*;

    fn meta() -> SourceMetadata {
        SourceMetadata {
            file_path: "readme.txt".into(),
            extension: "txt".into(),
            language: None,
            scope_id: "test".into(),
            source_version: "v1".into(),
        }
    }

    #[test]
    fn test_small_file_single_chunk() {
        let chunker = FallbackChunker::new(512);
        let source = "Hello world.\nThis is a test.";
        let chunks = chunker.chunk(source, &meta()).unwrap();
        assert_eq!(chunks.len(), 1);
        assert_eq!(chunks[0].content, source);
